Moreover, "mineral" has an exact synonym which is "mineral" itself and is relatedly synonymized with "Minerale", "minerales", "minerals", and "mineraux".

adenyl nucleotide is a type of purine nucleotide.
Guanyl ribonucleotide is a type of purine ribonucleotide and also a type of guanyl nucleotide.
Adenyl ribonucleotide is a type of purine ribonucleotide and also a type of adenyl nucleotide.
poly ethylene terephthalate polymer is a type of polyester polymer.
vinyl polymer is a type of polyethylene polymer.
polystyrene polymer is a type of vinyl polymer.
signalling molecule is a type of molecular messenger.
reactive nitrogen species is a type of nitrogen molecular entity.
Amorphous cellulose is a type of 1 4 beta d glucan and also a type of exopolysaccharide.
Crystalline cellulose is a type of 1 4 beta d glucan and it is also a type of exopolysaccharide.
emulsifier is a type of chemical role.
Aluminium cation is a type of metal cation and is also a type of aluminium ion.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:oxidising_agent rdfs:subClassOf :chemical_role ;
    :has_definition "A substance that removes electrons from another reactant in a redox reaction." ;
    :has_related_synonym "oxidant",
        "oxidants",
        "oxidiser",
        "oxidisers",
        "oxidising agents",
        "oxidizer",
        "oxidizers",
        "oxidizing agent",
        "oxidizing agents" .
text: An oxidising agent is a type of chemical role defined as a substance that removes electrons from another reactant in a redox reaction. It is related to several synonyms including oxidant, oxidants, oxidiser, oxidisers, oxidising agents, oxidizer, oxidizers, oxidizing agent, and oxidizing agents.
carbohydrate derivative is a type of carbohydrates and carbohydrate derivatives.
monosaccharide derivative is a type of carbohydrate derivative.
pentose derivative is a type of monosaccharide derivative.
branched chain amino acid anion is a type of amino acid anion.
1 1 diol is a type of alcohol.
ketone hydrate is a type of 1 1 diol.
A food additive serves as both an application and a type of food component.
one carbon compound is a type of organic molecular entity.
organic acid is a type of organic molecular entity.
trivalent inorganic cation is a type of inorganic cation.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:poison rdfs:subClassOf :biological_role ;
    :has_definition "Any substance that causes disturbance to organisms by chemical reaction or other activity on the molecular scale, when a sufficient quantity is absorbed by the organism." ;
    :has_related_synonym "poisonous agent",
        "poisonous agents",
        "poisonous substance",
        "poisonous substances",
        "poisons",
        "toxic agent",
        "toxic agents",
        "toxic substance",
        "toxic substances" .
text: Poison is identified as a type of biological role and is defined as any substance that causes disturbance to organisms through a chemical reaction or other activity on the molecular scale, provided a sufficient quantity is absorbed by the organism. Furthermore, poison is associated with several synonyms including poisonous agent, poisonous agents, poisonous substance, poisonous substances, poisons, toxic agent, toxic agents, toxic substance, and toxic substances.
A polysaccharide derivative is a type of glycan, a type of biomacromolecule, and also a type of carbohydrate derivative.
N alkylglycine is a type of glycine derivative and a non-proteinogenic alpha amino acid.
An organic molecule is both a type of molecule and a type of organic molecular entity.
exopolysaccharide is a type of biomacromolecule.
Divinyl chlorophyll a is a type of chlorophyll and also a methyl ester.
Divinyl chlorophyll b is a type of chlorophyll and also a type of methyl ester.
eukaryotic metabolite is a type of metabolite.
animal metabolite is a type of eukaryotic metabolite.
mammalian metabolite is a type of animal metabolite.
prokaryotic metabolite is a type of metabolite.
Iron sulfides are a type of iron molecular entity and also a type of sulfide salt.
iron 2 sulfides is a type of iron sulfides.
greenhouse gas is a type of chemical role.
propellant is a type of application.
ec 1 oxidoreductase inhibitor is a type of enzyme inhibitor.
ec 1 14 oxidoreductase acting on paired donors with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen inhibitor is a type of ec 1 oxidoreductase inhibitor.
ec 3 hydrolase inhibitor is a type of enzyme inhibitor.
ec 3 5 hydrolases acting on non peptide c n bonds inhibitor is a type of ec 3 hydrolase inhibitor.
ec 3 5 1 non peptide linear amide c n hydrolase inhibitor is a type of ec 3 5 hydrolases acting on non peptide c n bonds inhibitor.

ec 1 14 14 oxidoreductase acting on paired donors incorporating of 1 atom of oxygen with reduced flavin or flavoprotein as one donor inhibitor is a type of ec 1 14 oxidoreductase acting on paired donors with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen inhibitor.

ec 1 14 14 1 unspecific monooxygenase inhibitor is a type of ec 1 14 14 oxidoreductase acting on paired donors incorporating of 1 atom of oxygen with reduced flavin or flavoprotein as one donor inhibitor.
pathway inhibitor is a type of enzyme inhibitor.
fungal metabolite is a type of eukaryotic metabolite.
bacterial metabolite is a type of prokaryotic metabolite.
human metabolite is a type of mammalian metabolite.
ec 3 5 1 4 amidase inhibitor is a type of ec 3 5 1 non peptide linear amide c n hydrolase inhibitor.
raising agent is a type of food additive.
food packaging gas is a type of food additive.
Food propellant is both a type of food additive and a type of propellant.
fatty acid anion 28 0 is a type of saturated fatty acid anion.

A food component is a type of physiological role, defined as a physiological role played by any substance that is distributed in foodstuffs. This includes materials derived from plants or animals, such as vitamins or minerals, as well as environmental contaminants. Additionally, "food component" is synonymously related to "dietary component," "dietary components," and "food components."
environmental contaminant is a type of chemical role.

Refrigerant is identified as a type of application and is defined as a substance used in a thermodynamic heat pump cycle or refrigeration cycle that undergoes a phase change from a gas to a liquid and back. This substance is utilized in air-conditioning systems and freezers or refrigerators and is assigned a "R" number by ASHRAE, formerly known as the American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air Conditioning Engineers, which is determined systematically according to their molecular structure. Additionally, "refrigerants" is a related synonym for refrigerant.

Carbohydrates and carbohydrate derivatives are a type of organooxygen compound, defined as any organooxygen compound that is a polyhydroxy-aldehyde or -ketone, or a compound derived from one. They contain only carbon, hydrogen, and oxygen and usually have an empirical formula Cm(H2O)n; carbohydrate derivatives may contain other elements by substitution or condensation. Furthermore, carbohydrates and carbohydrate derivatives are also related to synonyms such as carbohydrates and derivatives, as well as carbohydrates and their derivatives.
olefinic compound is a type of organic molecular entity.
trivalent inorganic anion is a type of inorganic anion.
A divalent inorganic anion is a type of inorganic anion that is defined as any inorganic anion with a valency of two. It is also related to the synonym "divalent inorganic anions."
monovalent inorganic anion is a type of inorganic anion.
nodularin is a type of ether.
peptidoglycan n acetyl d glucosamine  is a type of polyol.
brevetoxin b is a type of ciguatoxin.
pheophytin is a type of phorbines.
Diatomaceous earth is a type of mineral that consists of silicon dioxide.
Elemental iron is a type of iron molecular entity and is also a type of elemental molecular entity.
iron 0  is a type of elemental iron.
crustacean metabolite is a type of animal metabolite.
daphnia magna metabolite is a type of daphnia metabolite.
daphnia metabolite is a type of crustacean metabolite.
chlorophyllide a 2  is a type of chlorophyllide 2.
n acylammonia is a type of carboxamide.
proteinogenic amino acid derivative is a type of amino acid derivative.
non proteinogenic amino acid is a type of amino acid.
amino acid derivative is a type of organonitrogen compound.
Non proteinogenic alpha amino acid is both a type of alpha amino acid and a type of non proteinogenic amino acid.
Pentose phosphate is a type of phospho sugar and also a type of pentose derivative.
Pyrite is a type of sulfide mineral and is also a type of iron 2 sulfides.
metal allergen is a type of metal atom.
aromatic carboxylate is a type of carboxylic acid anion.
skatole is a type of methylindole.

A geographic feature is a type of astronomical body part, defined as an astronomical body part that is delimited by physical discontinuities with its surroundings. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: macroscopic spatial feature.
A bedding plane cave is a type of cave characterized by a cavity developed along a bedding-plane and elongate in cross-section.

An anthropogenic geographic feature is the same as something that is the intersection of a geographic feature and something that, at least in part, formed as a result of anthropisation. It is a type of geographic feature and also a type of something that has formed, at least partially, due to anthropisation. An anthropogenic geographic feature is defined as a geographic feature resulting from the influence of human beings on nature. Additionally, it has related synonyms including "man-made feature" and "manmade feature."

Mine tailing, also broadly known as tailing, is a type of anthropogenic environmental material. It is defined as the materials left over after the process of separating the valuable fraction from the uneconomic fraction (gangue) of an ore.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

:administrative_region rdfs:subClassOf :site ;
    :has_exact_synonym "administrative area"^^xsd:string ;
    :has_related_synonym "administrative division"^^xsd:string,
        "administrative entity"^^xsd:string,
        "boundary region"^^xsd:string,
        "civil area"^^xsd:string,
        "district"^^xsd:string,
        "free trade zone"^^xsd:string,
        "governed place"^^xsd:string,
        "leased area (government)"^^xsd:string,
        "leased zone (government)"^^xsd:string,
        "neutral zone (political)"^^xsd:string,
        "prefecture"^^xsd:string,
        "protectorate"^^xsd:string,
        "sheikdom"^^xsd:string,
        "sultanate"^^xsd:string,
        "trade zone"^^xsd:string .
text: An administrative region is a type of site, which is exactly synonymous with an administrative area. It is also relatedly synonymous with various terms including administrative division, administrative entity, boundary region, civil area, district, free trade zone, governed place, leased area (government), leased zone (government), neutral zone (political), prefecture, protectorate, sheikdom, sultanate, and trade zone. These synonyms suggest a wide range of governance and administrative concepts associated with an administrative region.

A first order administrative region is a type of administrative region and also a type of something that constitutes at least part of a national geopolitical entity. It is defined as a primary administrative division of a country, such as a state in the United States. Moreover, it is related to synonyms such as countries, 1st order division, first level subdivision, and first-order administrative division.

A second-order administrative region is a type of administrative region and is also considered a type of entity that constitutes at least part of some first-order administrative region. It is defined as a subdivision of a first-order administrative division. Furthermore, it is related to synonyms such as countries, 2nd order division, second level subdivision, and second-order administrative division.

A third-order administrative region is a type of administrative region and is also considered a type of entity that constitutes at least part of a second-order administrative region. It is defined as a subdivision of a second-order administrative division. This region is also related to several synonyms including barrio, countries, 3rd order division, third level subdivision, and third-order administrative division.

A fourth order administrative region is a type of administrative region and also a kind that forms at least part of a third order administrative region. It is defined as a subdivision of a third-order administrative division. Additionally, it is related to and synonymous with terms such as countries, 4th order division, fourth level subdivision, and fourth-order administrative division.

A national geopolitical entity is a type of political entity characterized by having effective dominion over a geographic area. This entity is exactly synonymous with a nation and has several narrow synonyms, including independent nation, independent political entity, and independent sovereign nation. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with a country, political entity, and state.

A transport feature is a type of human construction and is also a type of something that at least participates in some usage of an environment for transportation. It is defined as a construction that enables the movement of humans, their animals, or their vehicles.
A garden is a type of anthropogenic geographic feature defined as an enclosure for displaying selected plant or animal life. It is related to and synonymous with park and cropland.

A hydrographic feature is defined as a geographical feature associated with water, which is the same as something that is an intersection of a geographic feature and something that is a union of something at least partially surrounded by liquid water and something at least adjacent to a water body. Furthermore, a hydrographic feature is a type of geographic feature and has a related synonym, fluvial feature.

A cave system is a type of surface landform and also a type of entity that includes at least a part of some cave. It is defined as a collection of caves interconnected by enterable passages or linked hydrologically, or as a cave with an extensive complex of chambers and passages.

A canal is a type of watercourse and also a type of entity that possesses some elongated quality. It is defined as an artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow, used for navigation, drainage, or irrigation.

An ocean is a type of marine, saline water body that is at least composed primarily of sea water. It is defined as a marine water body that constitutes the majority of an astronomical body's hydrosphere. Additionally, the term "ocean region" is related as a synonym to ocean.

The sea is categorized as a type of marine, saline water body that is at least composed primarily of seawater. It is defined as a large expanse of saline water usually connected with an ocean. Furthermore, the sea has several narrow synonyms including channel, closed sea, marginal sea, open sea, open sound, and open water.

A saline hydrographic feature is identical to a feature that represents the union of features at the intersection of a hydrographic feature and those at least adjacent to an entity that is at the intersection of a water body and features that are at least composed primarily of saline water and those that are at least partially surrounded by saline water. Furthermore, a saline hydrographic feature is categorized as a type of hydrographic feature. Additionally, it is defined as a geographical feature associated with water, having a salinity above 30 parts per thousand (roughly 35 grams per liter).

A saline lake, which is also known as a salt lake, and has related synonyms such as salina and soda lake, is a type of lake and a type of saline water body. It is defined as a lake whose water contains a considerable concentration of dissolved salts. This term is synonymous with something that intersects a lake and something that is at least composed primarily of saline water.

A lake is identified as an entity that intersects with several characteristics: it is a lentic water body, at least partially surrounded by a planetary landmass, and situated in a location that is both a depressed landform and part of a planetary landmass. Being a type of lentic water body, a lake is inherently connected with water bodies that are stationary or have limited flow. Additionally, its characterization as partly enclosed by land and existing within a depression on a landmass further refines its definition. A comprehensive definition of a lake is a body of water or other liquid of considerable size contained in a depression on a landmass.

In terms of terminology, a lake is closely associated with a variety of more specific or related terms. Narrow synonyms include 'catch basin,' 'open water,' and 'tarn,' which refer to specific types of lakes or similar water bodies. Furthermore, it shares related synonyms such as 'broad,' 'llyn,' 'loch,' 'lochan,' 'lough,' 'mere,' 'mortlake,' and 'pasteuer lake.' These terms highlight the cultural and geographical diversity in naming conventions for lakes, reflecting the broad spectrum of lake types and characteristics found globally.
A freshwater lake is a type of lake and also a type of fresh water body, defined as a lake whose water contains low concentrations of salts. It has the exact synonym "FreshwaterLake."

A river is a type of stream and it is also a type of something that is at least continuous with some river channel and adjacent to some river bank. It is defined as a stream which, through permanent or seasonal flow processes, moves from elevated land towards lower elevations through a definite channel, and empties either into a sea, lake, or another river, or ends on land as bed seepage and evapotranspiration exceed water supply. Furthermore, river has an exact synonym "rio" and a narrow synonym "braided river."

A stream is a type of watercourse, also broadly synonymous with watercourse and exactly synonymous with streams. It is characterized as a type of entity that must have some linear quality and be continuous with a stream channel. The definition of a stream is a watercourse that is linear and flows across the solid portion of a planetary surface. Narrow synonyms for stream include braided stream, fork (hydrographic), lode, millstream, stream bend, and streamlet. Additionally, stream has related synonyms such as Creek, beck, brook, burn (hydrographic), creek, and rivulet.

A reservoir is a type of artificial lake and is defined as an artificial body of water, often contained by a dam, constructed for the purpose of water storage. It is broadly synonymous with the term lake and has a more specific synonym, covered reservoir.

A well is recognized as an anthropogenic geographic feature, which is categorized under entities that at least partially consist of elements that are a combination of tunnels, depressed landforms, and boreholes. Additionally, a well is defined as a cylindrical hole, pit, or tunnel that is drilled or dug down to a certain depth from which water, oil, or gas can be extracted or brought to the surface.

Spring is a type of surface landform and also a type of something that at least partly comprises some solid surface layer. It is defined as a surface landform which provides an egress for groundwater or steam to flow out of the ground. Additionally, spring is synonymously related to seep.

A sand pit quarry is the same as an entity that intersects with both a quarry and an entity that is at least capable of a process which is the intersection of a material extraction process and having an output of sand. It is a type of quarry and also a type of entity that is at least capable of a process that combines material extraction with an output of sand. The definition of a sand pit quarry is a quarry from which sand is extracted. Additionally, sand pit quarry is synonymously related to sand pit.

fragment:
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

:watercourse rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:onProperty :continuous_with ;
            owl:someValuesFrom :channel_of_a_watercourse ],
        :lotic_water_body ;
    :has_definition "A flowing body of water."^^xsd:string ;
    :has_narrow_synonym "culvert"^^xsd:string,
        "dredged channel"^^xsd:string,
        "fork"^^xsd:string,
        "gulch"^^xsd:string,
        "gully"^^xsd:string,
        "gut"^^xsd:string,
        "gutter"^^xsd:string,
        "kill"^^xsd:string,
        "lode"^^xsd:string,
        "narrows"^^xsd:string,
        "overflow channel"^^xsd:string,
        "passage"^^xsd:string,
        "pup"^^xsd:string,
        "race"^^xsd:string,
        "ravine"^^xsd:string,
        "reach"^^xsd:string,
        "rill"^^xsd:string,
        "rivulet"^^xsd:string,
        "run"^^xsd:string,
        "runnel"^^xsd:string,
        "seachannel"^^xsd:string,
        "seaway"^^xsd:string,
        "spillway"^^xsd:string,
        "stream"^^xsd:string,
        "tideway"^^xsd:string,
        "wash"^^xsd:string,
        "water gap"^^xsd:string ;
    :has_related_synonym "awawa"^^xsd:string,
        "barranca"^^xsd:string,
        "beck"^^xsd:string,
        "branch"^^xsd:string,
        "brook"^^xsd:string,
        "course"^^xsd:string,
        "draw"^^xsd:string,
        "moat"^^xsd:string,
        "narrows"^^xsd:string,
        "narrows (hydrographic)"^^xsd:string .
text: A watercourse is a type of lotic water body, which is defined as a flowing body of water that is at least continuous with some channel of a watercourse. It has narrow synonyms such as culvert, dredged channel, fork, gulch, gully, gut, gutter, kill, lode, narrows, overflow channel, passage, pup, race, ravine, reach, rill, rivulet, run, runnel, seachannel, seaway, spillway, stream, tideway, wash, and water gap. Additionally, watercourse has related synonyms including awawa, barranca, beck, branch, brook, course, draw, moat, and narrows (hydrographic).

Dead cave is equivalent to an intersection of a cave and something that at least has the quality of being somewhat dry. It is a specific type of cave as well as a type of entity that possesses some dryness. Dead cave is distinctly separate from a live cave, indicating that these two types of caves do not overlap. Additionally, dead cave is defined as a cave without streams or drips of water and is exactly synonymous with the term "dry cave."

A wadi is a type of valley characterized by certain processes and qualities. Specifically, it involves processes that intersect with both water flow and water accumulation, and it possesses the quality of being discontinuous. Wadi is defined as a valley or ravine, bounded by relatively steep banks, which becomes a watercourse in the rainy season. It is exactly synonymous with "wadis" and has narrow synonyms including "wadi bend," "wadi junction," and "wadi mouth." Additionally, related synonyms for wadi include "arroyo," "coulee," "gully," "nullah," and "wash."

A bay is a type of coastal inlet, defined as an area of water bordered by land on three sides. It is also related to several synonyms including bahia, embayment, firth, inlet, sea loch, and sea lough.

A pond is a type of lentic water body and is defined as a body of water, usually of smaller size than a lake. It has an exact synonym "Pond" and a broad synonym "lake," while "pool (water body)" is considered a narrow synonym. Related synonyms for pond include "POOL," "millpond," "pond," "ponds," and "pool" as well as "pool (water body)."

Rapids are a type of hydroform and also a part of some streams. They are defined as an area of broken, fast-flowing water in a stream, where the slope of the bed increases (but without a prominent break of slope which might result in a waterfall), or where a gently dipping bar of harder rock outcrops. Additionally, rapids are synonymously related to both cataract and torrent.

Marsh is a type of wetland ecosystem, defined as a wetland ecosystem that includes communities of grasses, rushes, reeds, typhas, sedges, and other herbaceous plants, and may include low-growing woody plants. It has a broad synonym, "wetland." Additionally, related synonyms for marsh include "Marsh," "marsh," and "quagmire."
An irrigation canal is a type of canal, which is defined as an artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used for irrigation. Moreover, it has a broad synonym: canal.
A ditch is a type of artificial channel and it is defined as a small, human-made channel which has been dug for draining or irrigating the land.

A lagoon is a type of aquatic layer that forms part of, or is adjacent to, some coastal wetland ecosystems and shores. It is primarily composed of saline water. Lagoons are defined as sheets of saline water separated from the open sea by sand or shingle banks, positioned between an offshore reef, especially of coral and the mainland, or within a ring or horseshoe-shaped atoll. The terms "lagoons" and "laguna" are exact synonyms for lagoon, and it is also related to the term "barrier lagoon."

A fjord is a type of coastal inlet that is elongated and adjacent to slopes. It is formed as a result of glacial erosion processes. The definition of a fjord is a long and narrow sea inlet with high, steeply sloped walled sides, created during a period of glaciation.

A waterfall is a type of lotic water body, hydroform, and something that is at least part of some stream. It is defined as a sudden descent of water over a step or ledge in the bed of a river. Waterfall has exact synonyms including WATERFALL, force, linn, and waterfalls. Moreover, it has related synonyms such as cascade, cataract, fall, and falls.

A tidal creek is a type of tidal watercourse, defined as a tidal water channel. These creeks may often dry to a muddy channel with little or no flow at low tide, but often with a significant depth of water at high tide. Additionally, a tidal creek is broadly synonymous with a stream.
A drainage canal is a type of canal defined as an artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used for drainage. It is broadly synonymous with the term "canal."

A wetland area is defined as a vegetated area that overlaps a wetland ecosystem, essentially being an intersection of a vegetated area and something that at least overlaps some wetland ecosystem. It is a type of vegetated area and also a type of area that at least overlaps some wetland ecosystem. Furthermore, a wetland area is synonymous with WetlandRegion.
